fresh basil pesto recipe and can you freeze it i have fresh basil growing and now that the really hot weather is here i need to use it all and make pesto i'm looking for a good pesto recipe and also need to know if once it's made can i freeze it i have quite a bit of basil to use thanks cups packed fresh basil leaves cloves garlic cup pine nuts cup extra virgin olive oil kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste cup freshly grated pecorino cheese see cook's note combine the basil garlic and pine nuts in a food processor and pulse until coarsely chopped add the cup of the oil and process until fully incorporated and smooth season with salt and pepper if freezing transfer to an air tight container and drizzle remaining oil over the top freeze for up to months thaw and stir in cheese cooks note if using immediately add all the oil and pulse until smooth transfer the pesto to a large serving bowl and mix in the cheese Tofu Chili con carne French fries Pizza Curry Cheese Ice cream Recipe Pasta Jewish cuisine Idli Tea Italian cuisine Mayonnaise Cuisine of Brazil Garlic Cuisine of Denmark Cincinnati chili Korean cuisine In-N-Out Burger French cuisine Food preservation Gumbo Cuisine of the Philippines Cantonese cuisine Breakfast Hot dog Risotto Cuisine of Malaysia Bengali cuisine Bread Japanese cuisine Kosher foods Ramen Cuisine of Greece Coffee Barbecue Haggis Ketchup Peruvian cuisine Peanut butter Hamburger Russian cuisine Cuisine of Turkey Cuisine of Thailand Soul food Cooking Baklava Sichuan Pepper Chicken soup Sausage Black pepper Domesticated turkey Cider Oregano Muesli Hamster Sushi Tamale Butter Bagel Salad Polish cuisine Fondue Catalan cuisine Roman eating and drinking Olive oil Rum Cooking oil Meatball Kraft Dinner D__ner kebab Dal Pancake Food Rice pudding Cheesecake Yoghurt Potato Cuisine of Singapore Roast beef Sea ice Crayfish B__chamel sauce Carbon dioxide Omega-3 fatty acid Poi (food) Satay Veganism Stanley Cup Essential oil 